    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 9, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Meta Spent $14 Billion to Ship an AI Model That's Merely Good\n\nNine months ago, Meta bought 49% of Scale AI and made Alexandr Wang its first-ever chief AI officer. Today, the bill came due.\n\n- **The model:** Muse Spark is the first product from Meta Superintelligence Labs — a complete ground-up rebuild: new architecture, new data pipelines, new everything. It now powers Meta AI and will roll out to WhatsApp, Instagram, Facebook, and Messenger.\n- **The result:** Competitive with GPT-5.4, Gemini 3.1, and Claude Sonnet 4.6. Does not beat them. Meta's own benchmarks confirm this with a straight face. Also: it's closed source, ending the Llama open-source era entirely.\n\n*$14 billion and \"competitive with the competition\" is the sentence. Investors are apparently fine with this.*\n\n**Sources:** [Axios](https://www.axios.com/2026/04/08/meta-muse-alexandr-wang) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/08/meta-debuts-the-muse-spark-model-in-a-ground-up-overhaul-of-its-ai/) | [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/08/meta-debuts-first-major-ai-model-since-14-billion-deal-to-bring-in-alexandr-wang.html)\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 Anthropic Built an AI That Breaks Everything. Then Decided Not to Release It.\n\nClaude Mythos Preview found thousands of zero-day vulnerabilities in every major operating system and browser. Anthropic's response: too dangerous for you.\n\n- **The capability:** Mythos surpasses \"all but the most skilled humans\" at finding and exploiting software vulnerabilities. Tested on production software across every major OS and browser. It worked. Thousands of zero-days, discovered and documented.\n- **Project Glasswing:** No public release. Access is limited to 11 organizations — AWS, Apple, Broadcom, Cisco, CrowdStrike, Google, JPMorgan Chase, the Linux Foundation, Microsoft, NVIDIA, and Palo Alto Networks — to secure critical infrastructure.\n\n*\"We built something that could break the internet, so we're only giving it to the companies that run the internet.\" Reassuring.*\n\n**Sources:** [The Hacker News](https://thehackernews.com/2026/04/anthropics-claude-mythos-finds.html) | [VentureBeat](https://venturebeat.com/technology/anthropic-says-its-most-powerful-ai-cyber-model-is-too-dangerous-to-release) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/07/anthropic-mythos-ai-model-preview-security/)\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Gemini 3.1 Leads the Benchmarks at One-Third the Price. Everyone's Having a Normal One.\n\nFive frontier-class models are now within a few benchmark points of each other. This is called progress.\n\n- **The leader (for now):** Gemini 3.1 Pro leads 13 of 16 major benchmarks and ties GPT-5.4 Pro on the Artificial Analysis Intelligence Index — at roughly one-third of the API cost. 94.3% on GPQA Diamond. Google has apparently decided that winning on price-performance is a valid strategy.\n- **The field:** GPT-5.4 in three variants (Standard, Thinking, Pro), Grok 4.20 with real-time web access, Claude Sonnet 4.6 leading real-world work evals — all within striking distance. April 2026 is officially the most competitive AI landscape in history.\n\n*(Fine. Probably fine. The developers paying for all of this are repricing their budgets for the third time this quarter.)*\n\n**Sources:** [LLM Stats](https://llm-stats.com/llm-updates) | [Build Fast With AI](https://www.buildfastwithai.com/blogs/best-ai-models-april-2026) | [Renovate QR](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-models-april-2026)"
